. ./.eccc_setup_intel
or
. ./.eccc_setup_gnu

Before the first build:
. ./.initial_eccc_setup

make cmake
make build
make work

***For EC users other than Michel:***
cp -p -r scripts/* $GEM_WORK/
cd $GEM_WORK
./runprep -dircfg ./configurations/GEM_cfgs
./runmod -dircfg ./configurations/GEM_cfgs

The following environment variables are created (examples):
GEM_DIR=/users/dor/armn/cpi/raid/davinci/goas/gem-devel_ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199
GEM_GIT_DIR=/users/dor/armn/cpi/ords/gem/gem-devel
GEM_WORK=work-ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199
GEM_ARCH=ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199
GEM_COMPILER=intel

The structure is different whether the $storage_model env. variable exists:

$storage_model:
GEM_DIR=/users/dor/armn/cpi/raid/davinci/goas/gem-devel_ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199
in GEM_GIT_DIR:
build-ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199 -> /users/dor/armn/cpi/raid/davinci/goas/gem-devel_ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199/build
work-ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199 -> /users/dor/armn/cpi/raid/davinci/goas/gem-devel_ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199/work

no $storage_model:
GEM_DIR=/users/dor/armn/cpi/ords/gem/gem-devel
build-ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199
work-ubuntu-18.04-amd64-64-intel-19.0.3.199

